title.narrative: OUTPUT 5.3: GENDER EQUALITY

description.narrative: Output 5.3: Regional and national stakeholders have up-to-date evidence and analysis and increased capacity to develop policies and programmes focused on gender differences and inequalities., which contributes to Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: OUTCOME 5. EVERY CHILD HAS AN EQUITABLE CHANCE IN LIFE. The most excluded girls, boys and adolescents in LAC benefit from equitable policies, budgets and programmes to ensure they develop to their full potential in an equitable manner in alignment with the Sustainable Development Agenda 2030.
